description:
Hidden Nature - West Africa's Secret Wildlife Paradies | Wildlife Documentary

Watch 'The Creepy & Bizarre World of the Okavango Delta' here: https://youtu.be/5MDwmdS_V14

The archipelago of the Bissagos Islands is a dream destination. A labyrinth of 88 islands belonging to Guinea Bissau which have been recognised as a Biosphere Reserve by the UNESCO. A unique ecosystem owing to its biodiversity and abundance which is a treasure for biologists such as Raúl León who are passionate about the small creatures which pass unnoticed.

Enjoy stories about nature, wildlife, culture, people, history and more to come.
